com.rawva.structures.graphs

Interface Graph<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of elements (vertices) in this graph
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    WeightedGraph<V,W>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    WeightedHashGraph

    public interface Graph<V>
    A Graph is a collection that, in addition to storing objects, can store pairs of objects to represent associations between two objects.

    Terminology:

    Each object is a vertex and each pair of objects (o1, o2) is an edge from o1 to o2. An object o2 is called a neighbor of object o1 if and only if o1 has an edge to o2. We also say that o2 is adjacent to o1 if and only if o1 has an edge to o2. In an edge (o1, o2), o1 is called the tail and o2 is called the head.
    Author:
    Raymond Tang

      • addEdge

        boolean addEdge(V tail,
                V head)
        Adds an edge from the specified tail element to the specified head element. Returns true if the edge was successfully added to this graph after this call.
        Parameters:
        tail - the tail vertex
        head - the head vertex
        Returns:
        true if the edge was added to this graph after this call, else false
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if one or more of the arguments are null and this graph does not permit null values
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if some property of one or more of the arguments prevents the edge from being added to this graph
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the edge cannot be added at this time due to insertion restrictions

      • addVertex

        Parameters:
        elem - the element to add
        Returns:
        true if the element was added to this graph after this call, else false
        Throws:

        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the specified element is null and this graph does not permit null elements

        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the specified element cannot be added at this time due to insertion restrictions
